Git is required for keeping track of version control
Git is distributed on cloud
Git is used for collaboration. We can write our code and make it accessible for public
Git is used for tracking changes in the application code
Recovery of the code is done as earliest as possible.(if a new version of the code is having some bugs and not functioning well, we can then backout it to previous version as early as possible)

Download Git for windows-> https://git-scm.com/install/windows

Create a GitHub account-> github.com -> give signup using a email and provide a password. we also require a username should be unique

Create a new Repositiory- unique name. Make GitHub Repo as public
Ensure the Readme file is present
Readme file is a file where we can write a long description for our code-> Readme files tell us about the fuctionality of our program

To make connection to from GitHub to VScode
Go to folder where Git&GitHub is present in our File Explorer and open cmd from that location

Commands for First time use
# command to configure our GitHub into our system.   'Paste the below commands in cmd'
git config --global user.name "Rohith-Ravula"  ("Note: Rohith-Ravula is my GitHub username")
# configure email ID 
git config --global user.email "ravularohit45@gmail.com"
# paste the below command for color automatic suggestions
git config --global color.ui auto

Mandatory Commands
# Command for initializing GitHub
git init
# Command for making remote connection for our application "need to provide GitHub URL in the command" (GitHub-> Repo-> code (right side)-> Local-> HTTPS-> copy the URL)
git remote add origin https://github.com/Rohith-Ravula/Git_Python.git 

# To make a Pull Request 'PR'
# (We can reflect the things in GitHub to VScode editor using PR)
Navigate to VScode editor Top-> Terminal-> New Terminal (Git&GitHub)
# Command to make a PR from GitHub to VScode editor (commands should be given in VScode terminal)
git pull origin main

# To make a push requests
# We can move the files from VScode to GitHub
# Command to know the current status of our Git. "We can see untracked files"
git status 
# To add the untracked files in VScode to GitHub
git add .
# check the status of Git again
git status
# command to commit the files
git commit -m "commit message"

# command to push the changes
git push